== Sample Rails & XapianDb Application

This sample application demonstrates how to use XapianDb in a Rails application

=== Quick start

==== 1: Install the gems

bundle install

==== 2: Create the database with some random data to play

rake db:migrate
rake db:seed # takes long since it generates a lot of records

==== 3: Go and play :-)

rails s

=== Production environment

The production environment is configured to use beanstalk as a queue to serialize
index updates. Please refer to the XapianDb README to learn how to set up the
prerequisites
